    {
      "id": "A1KAfOyrcPggTrykH-ZUb",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1748.0332511995018,
      "y": 280.412481298322,
      "width": 756.2156982421875,
      "height": 855,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "2Eze7m3DBjRR-ECI1Ep_L"
      ],
      "frameId": "ekYTIiJUZz9m_CqNBe3ZO",
      "index": "ao",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1785342011,
      "version": 2011,
      "versionNonce": 1725795108,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784003599401,
      "link": null,
      "locked": true,
      "text": "Endpoint:/api/v1/login\nEndpoint:/api/v1/signin\nAuth: Not needed\nLogical steps:\n    1-User send a post request containing\n    (username, email, password and pfpURL)\n    2-Bcrypt for encryption of the password,\n    in case of logIn the password is compared\n    with the one in database.\n    3-JWT web tokens are generated, \n       access token and refresh token are \n       used.\n       AccessToken: contain ID, userName and\n        Email.\n        RefreshToken: contain ID.\n    4-User data (ID, userName, email, password\n    pfpURL) is saved on database.\n    5-Server send the resp back to frontend\n    with tokens and data in JSON.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Endpoint:/api/v1/login\nEndpoint:/api/v1/signin\nAuth: Not needed\nLogical steps:\n    1-User send a post request containing\n    (username, email, password and pfpURL)\n    2-Bcrypt for encryption of the password,\n    in case of logIn the password is compared\n    with the one in database.\n    3-JWT web tokens are generated, \n       access token and refresh token are \n       used.\n       AccessToken: contain ID, userName and\n        Email.\n        RefreshToken: contain ID.\n    4-User data (ID, userName, email, password\n    pfpURL) is saved on database.\n    5-Server send the resp back to frontend\n    with tokens and data in JSON.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
